CNCP v1 24010
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#4927: Using `defineComponent` in `<script>` with `<script setup>` takes type error",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:27:03.112837+00:00",
  "text": "Using `defineComponent` in `<script>` with `<script setup>` takes type error\n\nFor components which using both `<script>` and `<script setup>`, and using `defineComponent` in `<script>`, when I try to generate declaration files from the compilation results, type errors are issued.\r\n\r\n### Version\r\n3.2.21\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[sfc.vuejs.org/](https://sfc.vuejs.org/#)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nUse vscode to open any project which contains vue and typescript dependencies (can use `vite-create` to create a vue-ts project), then copy sfc js compilation result into a new ts file.\r\n\r\nThis is to simulate type diagnostic when generate declaration files.\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nNo type error occurred.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40221744/141090328-aa86e633-7f7a-4527-9b7a-b663df726f7e.png)\r\n\r\n`defineComponent` returned type is not assignable to parameter type.\r\n\r\nIn [official example](https://v3.vuejs.org/api/sfc-script-setup.html#usage-alongside-normal-script) is export a native object, it seems to be the best practice.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40221744/141089921-73ce983e-53c7-4ab2-b411-9a203578cdb4.png)\r\n\r\nIf so, there will be some warnings when the usage is not recommended?\r\n\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: script-setup"
  ],
